HEADWORD: Ambs-ace
<hw>Ambs"-ace</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>ambesas</ets>; <ets>ambes</ets> both (fr. L. <ets>ambo</ets>) +
<ets>as</ets> ace. See <er>Ace</er>.]</ety> <def>Double aces, the lowest
throw of all at dice. Hence: Bad luck; anything of no account or
value.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ambulacral</ent>⟦br⟧
